    "as well as align a transformed source to a target,",
    "The field, Fs!t, can contain errors if the target image contains missing or corrupted information.",
    "If we have a set of images, {M 1, …, M n }, we can make multiple measurements of the same displacement field using transitive alignment.",
    "Now we can use vector voting as an error correction procedure with the set of displacement fields,",
    "This assumes the Anna Karenina principle: correct transitive fields are relatively similar with other correct fields, while incorrect fields will be different in different ways."
